Guys, all you have to do is change the current call to that method by this one: $wa->RequestLastSeen(time()."-1", $dst);
The message ID is formed by a timestamp concatenated to -1, the server will keep the timestamp and increase the other number (1), request by request. -1 seems to be the start point of your very first request, and moves forward from there.

The result comes just like any other request, print_r( $buff ) and you will see it. However, the last seen info it's not coming in any format, is just the amount of seconds since the last user action: 

To get this info well formatted, try this out:

$lastseen = $data[0]->getChild('query')->getAttribute('seconds');
echo date( 'H:i:s', strtotime('now ' - $lastseen . ' seconds' ) ) . "\n";

