$wa->parse_last_seen($msg);

and it was printing the last seen time.

isnt there any function like this now?

Then you guys are not playing with the latest code. With the example I've provided earlier, you should get the last seen info as it is. Is how I'm seeing it.
The interactive mode enters into a loop that runs both, $wa->PollMessages() and $wa->GetMessages(); and the last one returns the response that is stored in $buff.

Another simple way to get that info is:

echo "\nLast seen $dst :";
$wa->RequestLastSeen( time() . "-1", $dst );
while( TRUE ) {
    $wa->PollMessages();
    $buff = $wa->GetMessages();
    if( !empty( $buff ) ) {
        print_r( $buff );
    }
    sleep(1);
}
exit(0);

Remember, the last seen info is presented in seconds since the last user action, ie: 300 (5 minutes), you may use the two lines I posted earlier to get the real date/time data.

